Writes formatted output to stdout. Returns the number of characters printed.
```c
printf("Hello %s, you are %d\n", name, age);
printf("%05.2f\n", 3.14);
```

Reads formatted input from stdin. Returns the number of items successfully matched.
```c
int n;
scanf("%d", &n);
char name[50];
scanf("%49s", name);
```

Allocates `size` bytes of uninitialized memory. Returns a pointer to the allocated block, or `NULL` on failure.
```c
int *arr = (int *)malloc(10 * sizeof(int));
if (arr == NULL) { /* handle error */ }
```

Deallocates the memory previously allocated by `malloc`, `calloc`, or `realloc`.
```c
free(arr);
arr = NULL;
```

Fills the first `n` bytes of memory area `s` with the byte `c`.
```c
memset(buffer, 0, sizeof(buffer));
memset(arr, -1, 10 * sizeof(int));
```

Copies the string `src` (including null terminator) into `dest`.
```c
char buf[50];
strcpy(buf, "hello");
```

Appends the string `src` to the end of `dest`.
```c
char buf[100] = "Hello ";
strcat(buf, "World");
```

Opens a file and returns a stream pointer, or `NULL` on failure.
```c
FILE *fp = fopen("data.txt", "r");
FILE *fp2 = fopen("out.bin", "wb");
```
